Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.72,0:02:01.49,Wing Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720.000000,717.750000)\be3\blur3}Tallgeese Destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.53,0:13:25.97,Wing Series Mid-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(844,365.1)}Mobile Suit Gundam Wing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.21,0:23:30.23,Wing Next Episode Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720.000000,760.500000)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.24,0:23:58.60,Wing Next Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\be3\blur3\pos(715.077000,713.250000)}Assault on Barge
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.59,0:01:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling me to get off?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.13,0:01:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sandrock!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.70,0:01:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, my dear Sandrock!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.05,0:02:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've confirmed the{\i0}\N{\i1}engineers' identity.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.18,0:02:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All five of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.82,0:02:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, ma'am!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.88,0:02:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As suspected, they were{\i0}\N{\i1}all involved...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...in OZ mobile suit{\i0}\N{\i1}development, in the past.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.92,0:02:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.59,0:02:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All five of them disappeared...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.23,0:02:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and have been missing{\i0}\N{\i1}since the Tallgeese development.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.86,0:02:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or rather, since completing{\i0}\N{\i1}the Tallgeese blueprint.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tallgeese?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.93,0:02:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the mobile suit\NColonel Zechs is using?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.04,0:02:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Also called the Leo Prototype?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.31,0:02:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, it was built twenty{\i0}\N{\i1}years ago.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.27,0:02:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it's still regarded as the{\i0}\N{\i1}most powerful built on Earth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.01,0:02:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Most powerful is hardly\Nthe appropriate term.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ma'am.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.28,0:02:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be the most powerful\Nunless all soldiers agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.52,0:03:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have them make us a suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.86,0:03:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A mobile suit that's more\Npowerful than the Tallgeese.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.79,0:03:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, more powerful than\Nthe Gundams!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.37,0:03:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, I've brought Colonel\NZechs here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.78,0:03:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.31,0:03:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Please excuse the small room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.45,0:03:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.65,0:03:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need that for\NColonel Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.99,0:03:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.95,0:03:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.02,0:03:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sorry to make you uncomfortable,{\i0}\N{\i1}Zechs.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.16,0:03:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't concern yourself,\NYour Excellency.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.23,0:03:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm prepared to face\Na court martial.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.60,0:03:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you continue\Nto be a strong force...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...for the Romefeller Foundation...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.80,0:03:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...I foresee no problems with\Nthe court martial.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.17,0:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A strong force?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Romefeller Foundation\Nis concerned about the Gundams.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.88,0:03:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the most powerful\Nmobile suits on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you continue to fight\Nas our knight...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...to defeat the Gundams?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.35,0:04:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your Excellency.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.42,0:04:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't believe I can follow{\i0}\N{\i1}Romefeller's ideas any longer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.09,0:04:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.16,0:04:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've been fighting the Gundams{\i0}\N{\i1}out of personal feelings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And that's something which{\i0}\N{\i1}has no place in a war.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My battle with the Gundams{\i0}\N{\i1}is over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.97,0:04:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, Zechs,\Nsacrifice your life for OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A guilty verdict in court\Nfor your conduct...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...would be a big blow to OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.71,0:04:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you died an honorable\Ndeath, soldiers would mourn...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...and develop a stronger\Nwill to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.02,0:04:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, the higher powers\Nin Romefeller will be satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The name Lightning Count\Nwill live on as a legendary hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Your death would have\Nthat much value to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.13,0:04:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you died, you'd be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.73,0:04:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell, Zechs Merquise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.54,0:05:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Once this ship has been\Nevacuated...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.54,0:05:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...fifty Aries and twenty\NCancers will attack it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.31,0:05:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be manned by\NAlliance survivors...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...trying to win the\NFoundation's attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.48,0:05:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard this mission is to\Nallow you to escape unnoticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...by the higher powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.02,0:05:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But given the enemy and\Nthe sheer numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.69,0:05:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...there's no room for escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.19,0:05:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.76,0:05:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a test in order to\Nsurvive as Treize's friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.06,0:05:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.86,0:05:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...I can't escape from what\Nhe has planned for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.94,0:05:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Commence simulation!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.72,0:05:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the mobile doll\Nsystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.22,0:05:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We used an old model\Nof the Leo.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.06,0:05:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we program them by remote.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But no such problem exists with\Nour Taurus space mobile doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.43,0:05:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,These would reinforce our\Nsoldiers, wouldn't they...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.87,0:06:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...Chief Engineer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they'll replace soldiers as\Nthe main force in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.91,0:06:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone's attacking us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.68,0:06:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not responding!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.55,0:06:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect target for\Nthe mobile dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.75,0:06:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Order to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.75,0:06:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy spy?! How foolish!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.16,0:06:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission from the enemy Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Treize!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.46,0:06:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.20,0:06:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Discontinue attack!\NStop firing!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.73,0:06:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd represent\Nhuman soldiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.77,0:06:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...and propose a battle\Nagainst the mobile dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.77,0:06:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hoping to die, Colonel Treize?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mobile dolls don't show mercy{\i0}\N{\i1}like a human soldier would.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.84,0:06:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If mobile dolls are superior,\Nthen I don't belong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.01,0:06:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we could vie for\Nsuperiority here and now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.65,0:06:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind; kill the Colonel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an order!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.79,0:06:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's trying to kill us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.70,0:07:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.13,0:07:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.80,0:07:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Chief Engineer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.33,0:07:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Treize Khushrenada.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.20,0:07:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Murder Tubarov!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.51,0:07:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.38,0:07:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.08,0:07:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, stop!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.22,0:07:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm assassinating you, under\Nthe orders of Colonel Treize!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.92,0:07:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Engineer Tubarov.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.36,0:07:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wars are about more than\Nfighting with mobile suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.00,0:07:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We claim victory.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I retract my order.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mobile dolls and soldiers both{\i0}\N{\i1}take their orders from humans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.17,0:07:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I ask that you place more value{\i0}\N{\i1}on humans and learn to love them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.05,0:07:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and return, Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.65,0:07:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not around to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.29,0:08:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...OZ will allow worthless\Nactions by worthless people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.79,0:08:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.53,0:08:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The shuttle that avoided\NOZ's surveillance!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.26,0:08:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.56,0:08:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This course isn't frequented\Nby OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.87,0:08:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can capture ourselves\Na Gundam sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.17,0:08:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,More accurately, a Gundam pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.61,0:08:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The shuttle coming isn't\Nequipped for mobile suit transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what do you plan to\Nachieve by restraining the pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.18,0:08:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundam pilot has returned\Nto space so it can fight OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.52,0:08:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're after the same enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.62,0:08:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll negotiate with the pilot\Nto join forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we hand the\Npilot over to OZ...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...in exchange for a guarantee\Nof our safety?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Negotiations are meaningless\Nwith an organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.33,0:08:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...that has a record of\Nplaying dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.13,0:08:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Our one and only chance\Nis to fight head on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Objects approaching at\Nhigh speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.37,0:08:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably OZ's Taurus\Nmobile suits!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.54,0:08:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's five!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We have twenty space Leos;\Nwe have the advantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:08:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you not to\Nunderestimate OZ!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ already knows\Nthat survivors...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.55,0:09:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...from the Alliance Space\NForces are hiding here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They CAN defeat us,\Nwith just five Tauruses!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.49,0:09:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fight for the survival\Nof the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let them get\Nthe Gundam pilot!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.26,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were the Alliance\Nsuits deployed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Flying object approaching{\i0}\N{\i1}the retreating troops!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.27,0:09:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.27,0:09:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundam?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.47,0:09:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Did these guys find one of the\NGundams that had left Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.34,0:09:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All enemy suits headed here{\i0}\N{\i1}are space battle Leos!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.11,0:09:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Provide the mobile dolls\Nwith all target information.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.05,0:09:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Take over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.18,0:09:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm going after the shuttle!\N- {\i1}Yes, sir!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.43,0:09:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now they can utilize\Nunmanned mobile suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They probably saw them\Nas a valid weapon in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.24,0:10:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...since the battleground\Nhas no obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.34,0:10:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Battling without getting your\Nhands dirty is merely a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.88,0:10:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Foolish are those who\Nstart wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But the blood shed during\Nbattle is never a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.72,0:10:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Foolish people see the bloodshed\Nand learn to regret their actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.26,0:10:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But once war turns into a game\Nit becomes mere entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.09,0:10:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish they'd just declare\Na winner to this game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.10,0:10:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then nobody would\Nhave to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.53,0:10:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming the opponent\Nhas the technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't lack the technology!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.70,0:10:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But soldiers sense the\Nresponsibilities of combat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.84,0:10:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...if they don't use automated\Nfunctions!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.71,0:10:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got the technology?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.28,0:10:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you could earn\Nthe right to live longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.15,0:10:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.38,0:10:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather die than construct\Nsuch a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.72,0:10:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Youngsters always want to\Nthink things out rationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.82,0:10:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But war itself is anything\Nbut rational.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to give you the\Nchance to build a mobile suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.73,0:10:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...superior to the Tallgeese\Nand Gundams you built.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intentions of\Nlending a hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.73,0:11:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...in a futile war drawn out\Non a game board.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Negotiations are over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.67,0:11:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.84,0:11:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Officer Nichol\Nis on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.04,0:11:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Nichol?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.04,0:11:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Colonel Une.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.21,0:11:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I intercepted the Alliance's{\i0}\N{\i1}transmission.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.08,0:11:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're gonna team up{\i0}\N{\i1}with a Gundam pilot!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Those imbeciles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.12,0:11:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wipe out all of them!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.95,0:11:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, ma'am!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.06,0:11:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They're fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.72,0:11:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Five suits at once?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The enemy suits' speed{\i0}\N{\i1}has accelerated to 8G!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.49,0:11:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's superhuman!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.77,0:12:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The main Alliance forces{\i0}\N{\i1}are demolished!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.10,0:12:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll seize the shuttle!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.07,0:12:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Seize?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.14,0:12:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.91,0:12:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need a Gundam\Npilot without his Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Kill him!\N- {\i1}Roger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.45,0:12:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.88,0:12:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand me the communication set!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.26,0:12:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is Quatre.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.49,0:12:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My good friends who have{\i0}\N{\i1}returned to outer space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.36,0:12:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's do our very best{\i0}\N{\i1}to protect the colonies.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's using Heero's frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.17,0:12:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an outstanding soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.31,0:12:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He has the ability to bring\Nthe five Gundam pilots together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.25,0:12:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My good friends who have\Nreturned to outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.89,0:13:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do our very best\Nto protect the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.73,0:13:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop them from firing\Nat the shuttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.19,0:13:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can have pity\Nfor your men.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.36,0:13:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we have an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.50,0:13:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd have thought we'd end\Nup making a Gundam for OZ?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.64,0:13:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to make a mobile\Nsuit better than the Gundams.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.38,0:13:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.68,0:13:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid is a Gundam pilot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.18,0:13:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's so young!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.49,0:13:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Captain!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All the Tauruses are{\i0}\N{\i1}headed this way!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.42,0:13:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.82,0:13:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight them as far away from\Nthe shuttle as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.69,0:13:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Roger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.73,0:13:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to let you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.63,0:13:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've caught up with the shuttle!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop attacking the shuttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.97,0:13:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All Taurus units, move away\Nfrom the shuttle's route!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.34,0:13:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop our attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.88,0:14:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Orders are to leave the\Nshuttle alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.38,0:14:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all free to roam\Nin space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.85,0:14:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But we must get rid of the\Njunk we find along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.88,0:14:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichol!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.75,0:14:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Blow it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.39,0:14:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.79,0:14:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Look after the space Leos and\NI'll head after the shuttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.57,0:14:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no word from the shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.57,0:14:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll start to clean up\Nthe route!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.18,0:14:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.81,0:14:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The shuttle just fired at a Leo!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.12,0:14:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Life on the shuttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.35,0:14:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All suits, destroy the shuttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fire!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.43,0:14:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Our forces don't have the\Nstrength to retaliate against OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.37,0:15:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure that young\Npilot can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.37,0:15:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly hope my instincts\Nprove to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.05,0:15:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do our very best...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.52,0:15:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,...to protect the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.30,0:15:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ride has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.97,0:15:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How did repairs on\Nthe Tallgeese go, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.04,0:15:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your people's help,\Neverything's in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.24,0:15:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.04,0:15:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.28,0:15:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The radar's picking up objects\Nfrom point 0430 behind us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.68,0:15:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.65,0:15:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just on time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.22,0:15:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means they're gonna\Nsink this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.58,0:15:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.62,0:15:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it your best shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.75,0:15:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to think,\Nbut, Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.39,0:15:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Win this battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.66,0:15:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.76,0:16:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Good-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get going, Tallgeese!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.94,0:16:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifty Aries and twenty Cancers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.91,0:16:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll prove they underestimated\Nthe value of my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.14,0:17:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How many more?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice move!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.76,0:17:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not gonna die yet!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.15,0:18:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize, stop following me\Naround!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Or else I'll just want to\Nfulfill your radical hopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This friendship of the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.30,0:18:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...will only last until the day\Nmy mask breaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer be your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.53,0:18:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell, Treize!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.77,0:18:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The planet in the solar\Nsystem...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.64,0:19:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...that miraculously gave\Nbirth to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We call it Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.88,0:19:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The year After Colony 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.98,0:19:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,With the colonies' development,\Npeople live in new surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to plentiful natural\Nresources...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...and cultivated technological\Nabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.89,0:19:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this new world is\Nnothing but an imitation...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.62,0:19:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,...of humankind's motherland,\Nthe Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.73,0:19:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were the colonies\Ncreated in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.16,0:19:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear the main purpose was\Ntechnological development...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.03,0:19:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...to enrich mankind's life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.87,0:19:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Did man start asking too\Nmuch from this fake world?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.51,0:19:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Its colony's self-sustained way of\Nlife is more stable than on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.84,0:19:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...since it lacks the risk\Nof natural disasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.88,0:19:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears that this\Nunlimited growth...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.15,0:19:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...was guaranteeing the\Neternal existence of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.96,0:19:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps there was an age...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.49,0:19:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...when people dreamed they\Ncould start anew in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.23,0:19:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's unthinkable that\Nthe colonies or mankind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.30,0:19:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...will ever forget the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.77,0:20:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the colonies'\Ntechnology bring to the Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.17,0:20:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of technology the Earth\Nwants most; military power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.98,0:20:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Destruction is in human nature\Nand can never be eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.18,0:20:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the colonies are developing\N a militaristic disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.09,0:20:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies cannot forget\Nthe Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.25,0:20:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth has great beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.76,0:20:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Animals known as humans\Nhave acquired such strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.99,0:20:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...that they want to control\Nthis planet for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.03,0:20:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,From the point of view\Nof an entire planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.67,0:20:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...the life of a living thing\Nlasts no more than an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.74,0:20:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end, mankind only\Nthinks of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.87,0:20:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.77,0:20:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The time spent by humans in\Nouter space has been a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, the ideal is\Njust a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.11,0:20:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This false pacifism.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.22,0:20:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This false living space.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Outer space is a breeding\Nground for even more battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:20:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wars claim many lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.13,0:21:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind hasn't forgotten\Nthe sorrow caused by wars...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.23,0:21:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...yet they haven't stopped\Nfighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.97,0:21:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The blood and tears they shed\Nare merely ceremonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.54,0:21:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,One can't speak of history...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...without referring to the wars\Nin each era as important events.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.28,0:21:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the pale pep talks\Nof fighting for peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.45,0:21:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...have been repeated\Nnumerous times in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies say they need\Narmaments to maintain peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.32,0:21:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no different from on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.19,0:21:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies think they've\Njoined the big boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.03,0:21:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They believed the bloodshed\Nwould lead...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.36,0:21:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's enough\NDuo Maxwell!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.13,0:21:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's avoid that subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.93,0:21:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's making your classmates\Nuncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.70,0:21:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel it was appropriate\Nfor your greeting speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.34,0:21:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Duo, please be seated\Nat the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So why do people fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.35,0:22:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning of existence\Ncould lie in their will to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.56,0:22:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,People feel accomplishment\Nthrough battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.79,0:22:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's also a fact that\Nthe ones actually fighting...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.26,0:22:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...are never perceived as\Nbeing tainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.58,0:23:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no glory or praise...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.12,0:23:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...for the Gundam pilots\Nreturning to the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.99,0:23:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Only orders to destroy OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.49,0:23:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Gundam Deathscythe battles\Nthe Tauruses in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.23,0:23:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But Duo is defeated and\Ntaken prisoner by OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.90,0:23:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To keep confidentiality, Heero\Nsearches for Duo to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.74,0:23:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 19,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.88,0:23:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"Assault on Barge".
